# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Project-specific: internal docs and planning (not for public GitHub)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Exclude docs/ by default, but re-include the operations guide, which is
# genuinely useful for readers on GitHub.
docs/*
!docs/operations.md
PROGRESS.md

# Local working artefacts — internal briefs and analyst reference docs
# kept on disk for the user but not for the public repo.
engine_*_brief.md
manual_download_reference.docx

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Project-specific: raw data and local DB
# (too large and/or source-owned; reproducible via scripts/download_sources
# and `python cli.py ingest ...`)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
data/
benchmarks.db

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Project-specific: generated outputs
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Default: output/ not tracked. Exception: the credit-risk report (Markdown
# for GitHub rendering + Word for download) and the model-input CSVs are
# committed so visitors and HR can see example output without running the
# pipeline. The glob auto-tracks future periods; the regenerable HTML stays
# ignored.
outputs/*
!outputs/README.md
!outputs/data/
!outputs/data/*.csv
!outputs/charts/
!outputs/charts/*.png
!outputs/reports/
!outputs/reports/Credit_Risk_Report_*.md
!outputs/reports/Credit_Risk_Report_*.docx
